verbs.description: skyjack (third-person singular simple present skyjacks, present participle skyjacking, simple past and past participle skyjacked)

entries.meaning: To steal or commandeer (hijack) an airplane, usually by threat of violence to the passengers and/or crew members.

description: From the brand name Skyjack, from sky +‎ jack.

examples: Concrete was placed continuously, with an observer in a skyjack above the column communicating with the pump operator to avoid overfilling[...]
